ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Study; The code for each individual study
Notes: e.g., the name of the study in multi-grant collections

ElementDescription: Whirls (sits or stands in one place and spins self around).
Pacing (Walks, skips, or runs in a repetitive course).
Rocks head, body back/forth or side/side
Toe walks (do not rate this if part of a game).
Risky or dangerous behaviors (Running away from the home standing on furniture, climbing bookshelves, etc.).
Touches or plays with own sex organs
Isolates self from the group (may remain with the group, but not show interest).
Grimaces (Funny or strange facial expressions, or odd facial movements).
Agitated, upset by loud or sudden noises
Agitated or upset by new activities
Repetitive movements with objects (such as waving objects, tapping objects, etc.).
Sniffs or smells self or objects
Says words, phrases heard in the past (echoed speech).
Delusions (false beliefs or talks about things that are not rational or real).
Hears things that are not there (e.g., hears voices that other people do not hear).
Sees things that are not there (don't count pretend play or imaginary playmates in rating this).
Makes sounds that are not words
Little or no response when spoken to
Uses words to organize and name things
Tells others what he/she needs, wants
